/* C:\Users\Edwin Boston\OneDrive\Desktop\III\COMPILER\BOOT\eval.iii
 *
 * III — THE DEFINITIONAL EVALUATOR (Theta-0, the Meaning Lift rung 0).
 *
 * Executes a .iii module DIRECTLY from the parse-AST — lex.iii + parse.iii +
 * ast.iii are its ONLY compiler inputs.  sema, sid, cg_*, emit, link are
 * deliberately NOT consumed: this TU is the independent meaning-bearer that
 * the compiled route is differentially pinned against (run_meaning.sh).
 * A divergence between this evaluator and the compiled binary is, by
 * construction, a defect in exactly one of {evaluator, sema, cg_r3, emit,
 * link} — the adjudication protocol is DOCS/III-MEANING-LIFT-MAP.md Theta-4.
 *
 * Value discipline (dynamic tags, sema-free):
 *   tag u64 = class | width<<8 | signed<<16 | pw<<24 | psg<<32 | pcl<<40
 *   class: 0 unit, 1 bool, 2 int, 3 ptr.  width 0 = suffixless literal
 *   (adaptive: adopts the typed operand's width; defaults to u64 at binding).
 *   Integers are stored NORMALIZED: unsigned masked to width, signed
 *   sign-extended to 64 bits.  Literal suffixes are re-read from the SOURCE
 *   BYTES via the node's physical position record (the parser drops them).
 *
 * Memory model: one flat world (malloc'd, zeroed).  Globals+strings, a
 * locals data stack (so &local is a real address), an operand stack, symbol
 * tables.  Program pointers are absolute host addresses inside the world;
 * every load/store is bounds-checked (an escape is TRAP 113, never UB).
 *
 * Coverage (rung 0, evidence-sized against the 122 extern-free corpus KATs):
 *   decls  : fn, const, var (scalar + [T;N] array), type alias; struct
 *            registered-but-unsupported (0 uses in theater)
 *   stmts  : let / let mut, local var, assign, expr, if/else, while, loop,
 *            break, continue, return, nested block
 *   exprs  : int/hex (suffix-typed), bool, string (payload address), ident,
 *            call (direct, recursion ok), index (array or pointer stride),
 *            field->UNSUPPORTED, binary (arith/bit/shift/cmp/logical
 *            short-circuit), unary (neg/not/bnot/deref/addr), paren, cast,
 *            sizeof (parser-resolved)
 *   for / match / metal / wavefront etc. -> clean UNSUPPORTED status with
 *   the node kind recorded (the gate prints it; the ratchet names its gaps).
 */

module eval

